/bin/bash -lc "cat > REQUIREMENTS.md <<'EOF'
# Requirements Baseline

## Product
- Name: Pet Vet Coding Puzzles.
- Platform: modern desktop browser only.
- Audience: beginner learners who can read simple instructions.
- Privacy: no personal data required for gameplay; no third-party auth required.

## Learning Scope
- Exactly 17 playable puzzles.
- Puzzle progression focus:
  - Puzzles 1-5: sequencing.
  - Puzzles 6-10: loops.
  - Puzzles 11-17: conditionals and mixed logic.

## MVP Functional Scope
- Puzzle lock/unlock progression.
- Block coding workspace with command library and active code area.
- Deterministic execution engine for connected blocks under "'`On Start`.
- Failure handling with `Oops` plus at least one hint mapped to explicit failure reason.
- Backend telemetry persistence for movement events and significant runtime/user events.
- Local analytics views with replay from persisted movement records.

## Backend Contract
Required HTTP endpoints:
- `GET /health`
- `GET /api/levels`
- `GET /api/levels/:id`
- `POST /api/session/start`
- `POST /api/session/end`
- `POST /api/events/batch`
- `GET /api/analytics/dashboard`
- `GET /api/analytics/puzzle/:id`
- `GET /api/analytics/events`

## Data And Persistence
- Puzzle data model fields required: `id`, `title`, `storyText`, `goalText`, `scene`, `grid`, `entities`, `availableBlocks`, `constraints`, `successCriteria`, `hintRules`.
- SQLite initializes automatically on first backend start.
- Required tables: `users`, `sessions`, `puzzles`, `attempts`, `events`, `movements`, `puzzle_progress`.

## Deterministic Constraints
- Execute connected blocks under `On Start` only.
- Disconnected blocks do not execute and trigger warning.
- Loop safety cap is mandatory.
- Collision failure reason is explicit and deterministic.

## Accessibility Baseline
- Large controls and clear labels.
- Keyboard navigation for major controls.
- Readable contrast.
- No critical information conveyed by color alone.
EOF

